{"parentUuid":"53e137bc-9a32-4ced-be7c-56d223caa86a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a1a2b12365cad33d6","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Lggv3g6wqy2LHw4MrfKRrm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SPGAzTriuDvoDWHFvrmxMr","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"Voyager skill library Minecraft LLM automatic curriculum"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1003,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5932,"cache_read_input_tokens":6421,"output_tokens":159,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5932},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1003,"output_tokens":159,"cache_read_input_tokens":6421,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5932,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5932,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":8289}}},"requestId":"req_011CcFqKKzMrmKhQcPDhbvcy","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"86fb5ee3-7ed4-4e8b-b956-5acf669dffa7","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:14:00.527Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"86fb5ee3-7ed4-4e8b-b956-5acf669dffa7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"a1a2b12365cad33d6","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SPGAzTriuDvoDWHFvrmxMr","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Voyager skill library Minecraft LLM automatic curriculum\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - MineDojo/Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/MineDojo/Voyager\"},{\"title\":\"Voyager | An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://voyager.minedojo.org/\"},{\"title\":\"[2305.16291] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2305.16291\"},{\"title\":\"VOYAGER: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2305.16291\"},{\"title\":\"[ML] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | by Ming-Hao Hsu | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@amiable_cardinal_crocodile_398/ml-voyager-an-open-ended-embodied-agent-with-large-language-models-b5efe4bca1ad\"},{\"title\":\"Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ehfRiF0R3a\"},{\"title\":\"VOYAGER: Revolutionizing Lifelong Learning in Minecraft with LLM Technology | by Suki | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@SukiLLM/voyager-revolutionizing-lifelong-learning-in-minecraft-with-llm-technology-ec99a1bf867b\"},{\"title\":\"Voyager: Skill Libraries as the Foundation for Lifelong AI Agent Learning - Beancount.io\",\"url\":\"https://beancount.io/bean-labs/research-logs/2026/05/08/voyager-open-ended-embodied-agent-lifelong-learning\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's comprehensive information about Voyager's skill library, Minecraft LLM, and automatic curriculum:\n\n## Overview\n\nVoyager is the first LLM-powered embodied lifelong learning agent in Minecraft that continuously explores the world, acquires diverse skills, and makes novel discoveries without human intervention.\n\n## Three Key Components\n\nVoyager consists of three key components: 1) an automatic curriculum that maximizes exploration, 2) an ever-growing skill library of executable code for storing and retrieving complex behaviors, and 3) a new iterative prompting mechanism that incorporates environment feedback, execution errors, and self-verification for program improvement.\n\n### Skill Library\n\nEach skill is indexed by the embedding of its description, which can be retrieved in similar situations in the future. When faced with a new task proposed by the automatic curriculum, the system performs querying to identify the top-5 relevant skills. Complex skills can be synthesized by composing simpler programs, which compounds Voyager's capabilities rapidly over time and alleviates catastrophic forgetting.\n\n### Automatic Curriculum\n\nThe automatic curriculum proposes progressively more challenging tasks based on the agent's current abilities, driving it to continually seek out new knowledge.\n\n### Technical Implementation\n\nVoyager interacts with GPT-4 via blackbox queries, which bypasses the need for model parameter fine-tuning. Code is used as the action space instead of low-level motor commands because programs can naturally represent temporally extended and compositional actions, which are essential for many long-horizon tasks in Minecraft.\n\n## Performance Results\n\nVoyager obtains 3.3x more unique items, travels 2.3x longer distances, and unlocks key tech tree milestones up to 15.3x faster than prior state-of-the-art. Voyager is able to utilize the learned skill library in a new Minecraft world to solve novel tasks from scratch, while other techniques struggle to generalize.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"dbd8ba9f-e3a8-4d8d-a4a0-d822afe1c363","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:14:09.735Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Voyager skill library Minecraft LLM automatic curriculum","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01EeoG8E2DKPFd75V96P9tqX","content":[{"title":"GitHub - MineDojo/Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/MineDojo/Voyager"},{"title":"Voyager | An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://voyager.minedojo.org/"},{"title":"[2305.16291] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291"},{"title":"Paper page - Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2305.16291"},{"title":"VOYAGER: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2305.16291"},{"title":"[ML] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | by Ming-Hao Hsu | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@amiable_cardinal_crocodile_398/ml-voyager-an-open-ended-embodied-agent-with-large-language-models-b5efe4bca1ad"},{"title":"Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ehfRiF0R3a"},{"title":"VOYAGER: Revolutionizing Lifelong Learning in Minecraft with LLM Technology | by Suki | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@SukiLLM/voyager-revolutionizing-lifelong-learning-in-minecraft-with-llm-technology-ec99a1bf867b"},{"title":"Voyager: Skill Libraries as the Foundation for Lifelong AI Agent Learning - Beancount.io","url":"https://beancount.io/bean-labs/research-logs/2026/05/08/voyager-open-ended-embodied-agent-lifelong-learning"}]},"Based on the search results, here's comprehensive information about Voyager's skill library, Minecraft LLM, and automatic curriculum:\n\n## Overview\n\nVoyager is the first LLM-powered embodied lifelong learning agent in Minecraft that continuously explores the world, acquires diverse skills, and makes novel discoveries without human intervention.\n\n## Three Key Components\n\nVoyager consists of three key components: 1) an automatic curriculum that maximizes exploration, 2) an ever-growing skill library of executable code for storing and retrieving complex behaviors, and 3) a new iterative prompting mechanism that incorporates environment feedback, execution errors, and self-verification for program improvement.\n\n### Skill Library\n\nEach skill is indexed by the embedding of its description, which can be retrieved in similar situations in the future. When faced with a new task proposed by the automatic curriculum, the system performs querying to identify the top-5 relevant skills. Complex skills can be synthesized by composing simpler programs, which compounds Voyager's capabilities rapidly over time and alleviates catastrophic forgetting.\n\n### Automatic Curriculum\n\nThe automatic curriculum proposes progressively more challenging tasks based on the agent's current abilities, driving it to continually seek out new knowledge.\n\n### Technical Implementation\n\nVoyager interacts with GPT-4 via blackbox queries, which bypasses the need for model parameter fine-tuning. Code is used as the action space instead of low-level motor commands because programs can naturally represent temporally extended and compositional actions, which are essential for many long-horizon tasks in Minecraft.\n\n## Performance Results\n\nVoyager obtains 3.3x more unique items, travels 2.3x longer distances, and unlocks key tech tree milestones up to 15.3x faster than prior state-of-the-art. Voyager is able to utilize the learned skill library in a new Minecraft world to solve novel tasks from scratch, while other techniques struggle to generalize."],"durationSeconds":8.588120290999301,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"86fb5ee3-7ed4-4e8b-b956-5acf669dffa7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"53e137bc-9a32-4ced-be7c-56d223caa86a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"a1a2b12365cad33d6","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JGUpHxzYfEe8u1diiYnZDq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Letta skill learning agent blog filesystem self-improving\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Blog | Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog\"},{\"title\":\"Skill Learning: Bringing Continual Learning to CLI Agents | Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog/skill-learning\"},{\"title\":\"Introducing Letta Filesystem | Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog/letta-filesystem\"},{\"title\":\"Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog-categories/research\"},{\"title\":\"Continual Learning in Token Space | Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog/continual-learning\"},{\"title\":\"New course on Letta with DeepLearning.AI | Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog/deeplearning-ai-llms-as-operating-systems-agent-memory\"},{\"title\":\"Rearchitecting Letta’s Agent Loop: Lessons from ReAct, MemGPT, & Claude Code | Letta\",\"url\":\"https://www.letta.com/blog/letta-v1-agent\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - letta-ai/skills: A shared repository for skills. Intended to be used with Letta Code, Claude Code, Codex CLI, and other agents that support skills. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/letta-ai/skills\"},{\"title\":\"letta-ai/letta-code: The memory-first coding agent\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/letta-ai/letta-code\"}]\n\nI found relevant information from Letta's blog about skill learning agents, filesystem features, and self-improving capabilities. Here's what the search results show:\n\n## Skill Learning\n\nLetta released Skill Learning, a way to dynamically learn skills through experience, enabling agents to use their past experience to actually improve, rather than degrade, over time. Skill Learning enables agents to learn and improve over time, without needing to change their underlying weights.\n\n## Filesystem Integration\n\nSkills are stored as .md files, designed to be modular and can be managed by git, making them a convenient way to share learnings across your organization. Letta Filesystem provides an interface for agents to organize and reference content from documents like PDFs, transcripts, documentation, and more, representing documents as folders and files to the agent, and providing filesystem-like tools to interact with file contents.\n\n## Self-Improvement\n\nLetta believes that learning in token space is the key to building AI agents that truly improve over time, driven by the observation that agents that can carry their memories across model generations will outlast any single foundation model. Agents programmatically rewrite their context to improve and adapt over time, including system prompt learning and skill learning.\n\nThe search results also mention Letta Filesystem scoring 74.0% of the LoCoMo benchmark by simply storing conversational histories in a file, beating out specialized memory tool libraries.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"276cdf51-4f1d-47e2-83e3-b10f22133a5e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:14:10.154Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Letta skill learning agent blog filesystem self-improving","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Tb1dUTt1G9e1bR3nk4RLrA","content":[{"title":"Blog | Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog"},{"title":"Skill Learning: Bringing Continual Learning to CLI Agents | Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog/skill-learning"},{"title":"Introducing Letta Filesystem | Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog/letta-filesystem"},{"title":"Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog-categories/research"},{"title":"Continual Learning in Token Space | Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog/continual-learning"},{"title":"New course on Letta with DeepLearning.AI | Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog/deeplearning-ai-llms-as-operating-systems-agent-memory"},{"title":"Rearchitecting Letta’s Agent Loop: Lessons from ReAct, MemGPT, & Claude Code | Letta","url":"https://www.letta.com/blog/letta-v1-agent"},{"title":"GitHub - letta-ai/skills: A shared repository for skills. Intended to be used with Letta Code, Claude Code, Codex CLI, and other agents that support skills. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/letta-ai/skills"},{"title":"letta-ai/letta-code: The memory-first coding agent","url":"https://github.com/letta-ai/letta-code"}]},"I found relevant information from Letta's blog about skill learning agents, filesystem features, and self-improving capabilities. Here's what the search results show:\n\n## Skill Learning\n\nLetta released Skill Learning, a way to dynamically learn skills through experience, enabling agents to use their past experience to actually improve, rather than degrade, over time. Skill Learning enables agents to learn and improve over time, without needing to change their underlying weights.\n\n## Filesystem Integration\n\nSkills are stored as .md files, designed to be modular and can be managed by git, making them a convenient way to share learnings across your organization. Letta Filesystem provides an interface for agents to organize and reference content from documents like PDFs, transcripts, documentation, and more, representing documents as folders and files to the agent, and providing filesystem-like tools to interact with file contents.\n\n## Self-Improvement\n\nLetta believes that learning in token space is the key to building AI agents that truly improve over time, driven by the observation that agents that can carry their memories across model generations will outlast any single foundation model. Agents programmatically rewrite their context to improve and adapt over time, including system prompt learning and skill learning.\n\nThe search results also mention Letta Filesystem scoring 74.0% of the LoCoMo benchmark by simply storing conversational histories in a file, beating out specialized memory tool libraries."],"durationSeconds":9.348924916000106,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"53e137bc-9a32-4ced-be7c-56d223caa86a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
